description:
&lt;p&gt;An exciting opportunity has arisen for an enthusiastic and motivated band 5 staff nurse to join our oncology day unit team on a fixed term basis for 6-8 months.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;On the oncology day unit, we are responsible for treating patients who have different types of cancers with chemotherapy and other types of SACT, as well as providing supportive therapies such as blood transfusions.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will ideally have 6-12 months post registration experience, venepuncture and cannulation skills, be IV and blood product competent and have a keen interest in oncology.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will be expected to provide and maintain high standards of care to our patients, be able to work autonomously as well as part of a cohesive team and have excellent communication skills.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The successful candidate would benefit from having some experience of working within oncology/haematology and experience in SACT administration, however training will be provided.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If this role is something you are interested in then please apply.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Laura Drury&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Tel: 02087255886&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Email: laura.drury0@stgeorges.nhs.uk&lt;/p&gt;
